E(X\mid Y=y)=\frac{n\phi(1-\delta)+(1-\phi)y}{1-\phi\delta}.
E(X|Y)=\sum_{x=0}^{n}xP(X=x\mid Y=y)
P(X=x\mid Y=y)=\dfrac{P(X=x, Y=y)}{P(Y=y)}
{n\choose x} \phi^x (1-\phi)^{n-x} {x\choose y}\delta^y(1-\delta)^{x-y}
\sum_{x=0}^{n}{x\choose y}\delta^y(1-\delta)^{x-y}
y
n-y
P(\text{faulty} \mathop{|} \text{passed}) = \frac{P(\text{passed}\mathop{|}\text{faulty})P(\text{faulty})}{P(\text{passed})} % =\frac{(1-\delta)\phi}{\phi(1-\delta)+(1-\phi)} = \frac{(1-\delta)\phi}{1-\phi\delta}
\begin{align} & E[X|Y=y]  \\ & = y + E[\text{number of robots that passed and are faulty}\mathop{|}y\text{ robots were faulty and failed}] \\ &= y + (n-y)P(\text{faulty} \mathop{|} \text{passed}) \\ &= y + (n-y)\frac{(1-\delta)\phi}{1-\phi\delta} \end{align}
